    q: 'Do I need a hammer drill for UK brick walls?',
    a: "Yes. Solid brick or blockwork needs hammer, or percussion, action. That's standard on any combi drill. A plain drill driver has no hammer mode and cannot break through brick or mortar. It will skid on the surface or snap the bit.",
  },
  {
    q: 'Cordless drill vs impact driver: which should I buy first?',
    a: 'Buy a combi drill first. It covers drilling, driving and masonry in one tool. That combination handles most UK DIY jobs on its own. Add an impact driver later, once decking, fencing or bulk screw driving jobs start slowing down a plain drill.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Can an impact driver drill holes?',
    a: 'Only roughly. An impact driver can turn a drill bit, but its pulsing action makes a hole hard to start cleanly and hold steady, and it carries no hammer mode for masonry. Use a combi drill or drill driver for an actual hole.',
